import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='Body_Mass__g_', by='Species', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of body mass across different species?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'], data['Beak_Length__mm_'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    ax.axvline(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["Beak_Depth__mm_"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('How does beak length vary with beak depth?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Species').mean()
    plt.bar(data.index, data['Flipper_Length__mm_'])
    plt.title('What is the average flipper length for each species?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    male = data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']
    female = data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']
    plt.hist(male['Beak_Depth__mm_'], alpha=0.5, label='Male')
    plt.hist(female['Beak_Depth__mm_'], alpha=0.5, label='Female')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of beak depth for male and female penguins?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
